The paper discusses the use of permissioned blockchains and game theory in designing trustworthy business-to-business market platforms. This work involves aspects of cryptography (cs.CR), game theory (cs.GT), distributed computing (cs.DC), databases (cs.DB), and software engineering (cs.SE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CR and cs.GT, followed by cs.DC, cs.DB, and cs.SE.
